Firefox Installer it's a script to make easy the installation of Firefox in Debian.

Available in English and Spanish by now.

Programmer: Martin "Zironid"				zironid@lavabit.com
Translator & Redactor: David "Pythism"		dfas98@gmail.com

To run the script you must give it execute permissions.

From a graphical file manager, right click on the script,
 go to the "Permissions" tab and click on the cell 
"Let execute this file like a program" (or similar).

After that you can double click it, and chouse "Execute in terminal".

Or from a command line:

chmod +x /path/firefox-installer.sh

And for execute the script:

./path/firefox-installer.sh
